import numpy as np

def priority_v2(item: float, bins_remain_cap: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    """Combines best-fit with adaptive temperature-scaled softmax exploration."""
    n_bins = len(bins_remain_cap)
    possible_bins = bins_remain_cap >= item
    if not np.any(possible_bins):
        return np.zeros(n_bins)

    remaining_capacities = bins_remain_cap[possible_bins]
    fit_scores = - (bins_remain_cap[possible_bins] - item)
    bin_utilizations = 1.0 - (bins_remain_cap / np.max(bins_remain_cap))
    temperature = 1.0 / (1.0 + np.mean(bin_utilizations))
    temperature = max(0.1, min(1.0, temperature))
    probabilities = np.exp(fit_scores / temperature) / np.sum(np.exp(fit_scores / temperature))
    priorities = np.zeros(n_bins)
    priorities[possible_bins] = probabilities
    best_bin_index = np.argmax(priorities)
    priorities[best_bin_index] *= 1.2
    return priorities

import numpy as np

def priority_v2(item: float, bins_remain_cap: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    """Combines best-fit with temperature-scaled softmax, adapting temperature based on bin utilization and adding a bonus to the best bin."""
    n_bins = len(bins_remain_cap)
    possible_bins = bins_remain_cap >= item
    if not np.any(possible_bins):
        return np.zeros(n_bins)

    waste = bins_remain_cap[possible_bins] - item
    fit_quality = waste / item
    temperature = 0.1 * np.mean(bins_remain_cap[possible_bins]) + 0.1
    normalized_fit = 1.0 / (fit_quality + 1e-6)
    exp_values = np.exp(normalized_fit / temperature)
    softmax_values = exp_values / np.sum(exp_values)
    priorities = np.zeros_like(bins_remain_cap)
    priorities[possible_bins] = softmax_values
    best_bin_index = np.argmax(priorities[possible_bins])
    best_bin_index = np.where(possible_bins)[0][best_bin_index]
    priorities[best_bin_index] += 0.5
    return priorities

import numpy as np

def priority_v2(item: float, bins_remain_cap: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    n_bins = len(bins_remain_cap)
    priorities = np.zeros(n_bins)
    possible_bins = bins_remain_cap >= item
    if not np.any(possible_bins):
        return priorities
    
    remaining_capacities = bins_remain_cap[possible_bins]
    
    bin_utilization = 1 - (bins_remain_cap / np.max(bins_remain_cap))
    
    
    fit_scores = 1.0 / (remaining_capacities - item + 1e-6)
    
    exploration_bonus = 0.1 * (1 - bin_utilization)
    
    priorities[possible_bins] = fit_scores + exploration_bonus
    
    best_bin_index = np.argmax(priorities[possible_bins])
    
    priorities[possible_bins] = 0.0
    priorities[possible_bins[best_bin_index]] = 1.0
    
    return priorities
